    "description": [
      "Two small, huddled forms rest in the crook of an old, tall spruce's roots, locked in an embrace.  They are unmoving and their rime-traced flesh is a terrible shade of blue.  There is an incongruous tranquility to the area as nature seems to observe the doomed pair in silence.  Even the raging of the wind is but a distant whistle."
